Short-circuit clash handling under ClashStrategy::PressAll.

handle_clashes() runs the full O(actions^2) possible_clashes() pair scan
(decompose() allocations per pair, rebuilt every call, every frame, per
InputMap) BEFORE the strategy is consulted; PressAll only nulls each
clash inside resolve_clash(). With PressAll the whole pass is a
semantic no-op, so return before scanning. Measured 2-4% of frame CPU
in Ambition desktop profiling (desktop-lifecycle-5) with a single
~20-action map and zero chords.

Apply to a fork of leafwing-input-manager v0.20.0, then wire it in the
workspace [patch.crates-io] exactly like the bevy_ggrs entry. Ambition
side is already ready: tune_clash_strategy_to_bindings (ambition_host)
keeps the strategy PressAll while no chord exists.

--- a/src/clashing_inputs.rs
+++ b/src/clashing_inputs.rs
@@ -173,6 +173,11 @@ impl<A: Actionlike> InputMap<A> {
     pub fn handle_clashes(
         &self,
         updated_actions: &mut UpdatedActions<A>,
         input_store: &CentralInputStore,
         clash_strategy: ClashStrategy,
         gamepad: Entity,
     ) {
+        // PressAll never culls anything: every resolve_clash() call below
+        // would return None. Skip the O(actions^2) clash scan entirely.
+        if clash_strategy == ClashStrategy::PressAll {
+            return;
+        }
         for clash in self.get_clashes(updated_actions, input_store, gamepad) {
